    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Bad array declarator: To declare a managed array the rank specifier precedes the variable&apos;s identifier. To declare a fixed size buffer field, use the fixed keyword before the field type.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">An array was declared incorrectly. In X#, unlike in C and C++, the square brackets follow the type, not the variable name. Also, realize that the syntax for a fixed size buffer differs from that of an array.</text></para>
